  "texts": [
    "For a simplified visualisation of how a graph neural network would process such an input, refer to Fig. 1A.",
    "To construct the input graphs, we first aligned the four data sources with respect to their game IDs and timestamps and filtered out 2517 invalid corner kicks, for which the alignment failed due to missing data, e.g., missing tracking frames or event labels.",
    "This filtering yielded 7176 valid corner kicks for training and evaluation.",
    "We summarised the exact information that was used to construct the input graphs in Table 2.",
    "In particular, other than player heights (measured in centimeters (cm)) and weights (measured in kilograms (kg)), the players were anonymous in the model."
  ],
